  <title>Statistics model element</title>
      <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css"></link>
  </head>
  <body">
    <h2>
      <img src="./Statistics.gif"> Data Reader model element 
    </h2>
    <p>
      Statistics stores a number of double values and computes descriptive statistics out of them.
    </p>
    <p> The element is based on capabilities provided by the <a href=" ">Apache Common numerics library</a>.
    <h3>Usage</h3>
      <p>
      To add a statictics element to your model, simply drag the icon element to the list of your model elements.
      </p>
    <p>
    A call to the element method <i>void addValue(double value)</i> adds a double value to the dataset.
    </p>
    <p>
    A call to the element method <i>void clear()</i> clears all data previously added.
    </p>
    <p>
    The element provides the folowing methods to retrieve descriptive statistics out of the data added:
    <ul>
      <li> <i>double getMean()</i> Returns the mean value of the dataset </li>
      <li> <i>double getVariance()</i> Returns the variance of the dataset </li>
    </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
    The folowing methods allow you to compute statistics directly from an array of double values:
    <ul>
      <li> <i>double getMean(double[] values)</i> Returns the mean value of the elements of the array </li>
      <li> <i>double getVariance(double[] values)</i> Returns the variance of the elements of the array</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
